WEBVTT

00:03.421 --> 00:06.424
[Showtime fanfare]

00:08.175 --> 00:09.844
[scoffs]
You've got to be kidding me.

00:09.844 --> 00:11.929
You don't remember what happened
to us last season?

00:11.929 --> 00:15.182
What are you, some kind
of fucking idiot?

00:15.182 --> 00:17.101
♪ rock music ♪

00:17.101 --> 00:19.103
- [Liam] You got married?
- [Fiona] Yeah.

00:19.103 --> 00:21.397
Well, are you happy, or...

00:21.397 --> 00:22.857
Gus seems like a good guy.

00:22.857 --> 00:25.110
Something is going on with us.
We both know it.

00:25.110 --> 00:26.861
[Sean] Well, I don't want
to be that shithead

00:26.861 --> 00:28.070
who's sleeping
with some nice guy's wife.

00:28.070 --> 00:29.447
What if Gus and I split up?

00:29.447 --> 00:31.198
♪♪♪

00:31.198 --> 00:33.117
I think I'm falling in love
with one of my professors.

00:33.117 --> 00:35.494
Helene--you know,
she knows what she wants.

00:35.494 --> 00:36.704
She doesn't second-guess
herself.

00:36.704 --> 00:38.038
It's really sexy.

00:38.038 --> 00:39.165
See if it's safe to leave?

00:39.165 --> 00:41.792
♪♪♪

00:41.792 --> 00:44.087
- I want to have sex with you.
- We don't need that.

00:44.087 --> 00:46.338
- I'm on the pill.
- Cool.

00:46.338 --> 00:48.549
[Fiona] You can't have a boy
in your bed.

00:48.549 --> 00:49.884
- You do.
- I'm a grown-up.

00:49.884 --> 00:50.926
[Debbie] I'm pregnant.

00:50.926 --> 00:52.095
[Fiona] Are you sure?

00:52.095 --> 00:54.013
Oh, shit.

00:54.013 --> 00:56.099
Why are you taping horse
to my tummy?

00:56.099 --> 00:58.476
'Cause I'm your uncle,
and you do what I say.

00:58.476 --> 01:00.394
- [dog barking]
- Carl?

01:00.394 --> 01:02.062
[Gaither] I sentence you
to the maximum:

01:02.062 --> 01:03.731
one year at the Illinois
Department of Corrections

01:03.731 --> 01:05.107
Juvenile Justice Division.

01:05.107 --> 01:06.692
Don't you worry.

01:06.692 --> 01:10.112
No one's gonna mess
with you again.

01:10.112 --> 01:11.071
Let's do this.

01:12.323 --> 01:14.116
- Whoo!

01:14.116 --> 01:16.076
- What the hell happened?
- He's crazy. He steal baby.

01:16.076 --> 01:19.997
[Beard] Bipolar one, acute mania
with psychotic features.

01:19.997 --> 01:21.749
- This means--
- No, we know what it means.

01:21.749 --> 01:24.084
I hate the meds.
You gonna make me take them?

01:24.084 --> 01:25.961
You get fucking nuts
when you don't.

01:25.961 --> 01:27.880
You can't fix me,
'cause I'm not broken.

01:27.880 --> 01:29.340
I don't need
to be fixed, okay?

01:29.340 --> 01:30.966
This is you
breaking up with me.

01:30.966 --> 01:32.092
[Sammi] Mickey.

01:32.092 --> 01:34.179
Holy shit.

01:34.179 --> 01:35.305
[gunshot]

01:35.305 --> 01:36.306
Fuck you!

01:36.306 --> 01:40.935
[both yelling indistinctly]

01:40.935 --> 01:41.852
[siren wails]

01:41.852 --> 01:43.437
That can't be good.

01:43.437 --> 01:45.022
Oh, I need a drink.

01:45.022 --> 01:46.191
What's the occasion?

01:46.191 --> 01:47.858
Cancer.

01:47.858 --> 01:49.860
I've seen what chemo
does to a body.

01:49.860 --> 01:52.071
It's not a battle.
That's a lost cause.

01:52.071 --> 01:54.448
Dying is lonely.
We know that.

01:54.448 --> 01:55.741
Doesn't have to be.

01:55.741 --> 01:57.409
Thank you.

01:57.409 --> 01:59.954
[Frank] For what?

01:59.954 --> 02:01.997
[Bianca] You've made me happy.

02:01.997 --> 02:04.166
[Frank] Bianca!

02:05.501 --> 02:08.504
[waves lapping]

02:16.387 --> 02:19.390
♪ rock music ♪

02:19.390 --> 02:23.352
♪♪♪

02:23.352 --> 02:26.730
♪ Think of all
the luck you got ♪

02:26.730 --> 02:29.858
♪ Know that
it's not for naught ♪

02:29.858 --> 02:32.987
♪ You were beaming
once before ♪

02:32.987 --> 02:37.408
♪ But it's not like that
anymore ♪

02:37.408 --> 02:40.661
♪ What is this downside ♪

02:40.661 --> 02:44.164
♪ That you speak of? ♪

02:44.164 --> 02:46.250
♪ What is this feeling ♪

02:46.250 --> 02:50.921
♪ You're so sure of? ♪

02:50.921 --> 02:55.926
♪♪♪

02:57.886 --> 03:01.098
♪ Round up
the friends you got ♪

03:01.098 --> 03:04.227
♪ Know that
they're not for naught ♪

03:04.227 --> 03:07.438
♪ You were willing
once before ♪

03:07.438 --> 03:11.817
♪ But it's not like that
anymore ♪

03:11.817 --> 03:15.154
♪ What is this downside ♪

03:15.154 --> 03:18.782
♪ That you speak of? ♪

03:18.782 --> 03:20.659
♪ What is this feeling ♪

03:20.659 --> 03:24.371
♪ You're so sure of? ♪

03:25.372 --> 03:28.375
[sprinkler clicking]

03:28.375 --> 03:31.378
♪ somber guitar music ♪

03:31.378 --> 03:36.383
♪♪♪

03:47.936 --> 03:50.939
♪ mellow rock music ♪

03:50.939 --> 03:55.986
♪♪♪

04:03.285 --> 04:06.246
Hey.

04:06.246 --> 04:08.416
Hey!

04:08.416 --> 04:09.208
Hey!

04:12.127 --> 04:13.463
[sighs]

04:14.421 --> 04:15.881
Come on, man.

04:15.881 --> 04:18.634
We talked about this.

04:18.634 --> 04:20.303
Look, I'm sorry
for your loss,

04:20.303 --> 04:22.638
but you can't keep
sleeping here.

04:24.848 --> 04:26.892
Look, you need to get on
with your life, man.

04:26.892 --> 04:28.394
That's what your daughter
would've wanted.

04:28.394 --> 04:29.853
She wasn't my daughter.

04:29.853 --> 04:32.690
She was the love of my life.

04:32.690 --> 04:34.942
My sun, my moon,

04:34.942 --> 04:38.153
my dusk, my dawn.

04:38.153 --> 04:40.364
The spring in my step,

04:40.364 --> 04:42.658
the syrup on my waffle...

04:45.077 --> 04:47.121
...the Tootsie in my pop.

04:49.707 --> 04:52.126
Look, man, I got a grave
to dig right over there,

04:52.126 --> 04:54.712
and you can't be here
when the funeral party shows up.

05:01.301 --> 05:04.389
Have a good day, my love.

05:04.389 --> 05:05.848
I'll see you tonight.

05:08.183 --> 05:09.184
[whimpers]

05:11.270 --> 05:12.688
[hip-hop ringtone playing]

05:12.688 --> 05:14.898
♪ Hip-hop ♪

05:14.898 --> 05:16.191
♪ Gonna live ♪

05:18.736 --> 05:19.862
[groans]

05:19.862 --> 05:21.572
Time to get up, old man.

05:23.991 --> 05:26.994
♪ upbeat rock music ♪

05:26.994 --> 05:31.331
♪♪♪

05:31.331 --> 05:32.750
[light knock on door]
[Debbie] Occupied!

05:32.750 --> 05:34.752
♪♪♪

05:34.752 --> 05:36.128
Time for work.

05:36.128 --> 05:38.172
Don't forget
to take your meds.

05:38.172 --> 05:40.215
[growls and smooches]

05:40.215 --> 05:41.592
Up and at them, Bean.

05:43.343 --> 05:45.053
[Debbie] Ugh, use
the downstairs toilet

05:45.053 --> 05:46.556
if you're so fucking desperate.

05:46.556 --> 05:48.140
We got to be at the clinic
before 8:00

05:48.140 --> 05:50.434
or we're gonna be waiting
all day.

05:50.434 --> 05:52.060
We're doing this today, Debs.

05:52.060 --> 05:56.190
We got to know for sure
one way or another.

05:56.190 --> 05:57.065
Debbie.

05:57.065 --> 05:58.401
[Debbie] I heard you.

06:00.652 --> 06:01.862
Is she gonna go?

06:01.862 --> 06:05.365
Oh, she's going.

06:05.365 --> 06:08.827
How are you today,
Mrs. P-fender?

06:08.827 --> 06:12.623
The P is silent,
and stop calling me that.

06:12.623 --> 06:14.041
You're still married,
though, right?

06:14.041 --> 06:15.543
Separated.

06:15.543 --> 06:17.753
- Sounds like a "yes."
- [chuckles]

06:17.753 --> 06:20.255
You're the one sleeping
with a married woman.

06:20.255 --> 06:22.382
What's that make you?

06:22.382 --> 06:23.383
Lucky.

06:23.383 --> 06:24.259
♪♪♪

06:24.259 --> 06:25.553
♪ Oh, eh ♪

06:25.553 --> 06:27.430
Frank's gonna
burn the house down.

06:27.430 --> 06:29.640
♪ I'm never gonna feel,
go and take my soul ♪

06:29.640 --> 06:32.017
♪ Keep protecting
what is good ♪

06:32.017 --> 06:34.144
Go away!
Oh, my God.

06:34.144 --> 06:37.648
♪ The only thing
that's on my mind ♪

06:37.648 --> 06:39.441
♪ Yeah, you're looking
all around ♪

06:39.441 --> 06:42.402
♪ All across the land ♪

06:42.402 --> 06:45.490
♪ Now you're never, ever, ever
gonna understand ♪

06:45.490 --> 06:48.408
♪♪♪

06:48.408 --> 06:49.409
Don't you have to open today?

06:49.409 --> 06:51.912
- [groans]
- What is he doing?

06:51.912 --> 06:54.499
- Weeping, I think.
- Are you weeping again, Frank?

06:54.499 --> 06:57.835
It's called mourning a loved one
taken too soon.

06:57.835 --> 06:59.920
- You want a lift to work?
- No.

06:59.920 --> 07:02.506
Your shift starts
in half an hour.

07:02.506 --> 07:03.590
Meds?

07:03.590 --> 07:05.551
Yes, Mom.

07:05.551 --> 07:07.427
I'm not your mother.
I'm just concerned.

07:07.427 --> 07:09.054
Did you take them?

07:09.054 --> 07:10.931
[gasps]
Fuck, Frank.

07:10.931 --> 07:12.600
I love you.

07:12.600 --> 07:16.395
I--I just want you to know
I'm--I love you.

07:16.395 --> 07:19.231
I ever tell you about the time
I caught an octopus on the reef

07:19.231 --> 07:21.316
outside of our hut
and Bianca cooked it

07:21.316 --> 07:22.860
on an open fire
right on the beach?

07:22.860 --> 07:24.695
- Yes.
- Yes.

07:24.695 --> 07:27.781
And the funny little sneeze she
would do when she was asleep?

07:27.781 --> 07:28.907
[all imitate Bianca's sneeze]

07:30.868 --> 07:33.078
- Debs, I love you.
- Jesus.

07:33.078 --> 07:34.788
I just--I want you to know that.

07:34.788 --> 07:36.582
Go away, Frank.

07:36.582 --> 07:38.292
You almost ready to go, Debs?

07:38.292 --> 07:39.918
- I'm eating.
- Well, eat faster.

07:39.918 --> 07:41.920
We got to drop Liam off
at pre-K on the way.

07:41.920 --> 07:44.298
Has anyone seen
my black armband?

07:44.298 --> 07:46.133
She's dead, Frank.

07:46.133 --> 07:48.093
She--

07:48.093 --> 07:49.595
Jesus.

07:49.595 --> 07:51.346
What's the matter
with you people?

07:51.346 --> 07:52.764
She was my soul mate.

07:52.764 --> 07:55.392
She probably killed herself
just to get away from you.

07:55.392 --> 07:56.852
Can I borrow five bucks?

07:56.852 --> 07:58.520
No.

07:58.520 --> 08:00.272
- Debs?
- For what?

08:00.272 --> 08:02.190
I--I want to light a candle
for Bianca

08:02.190 --> 08:03.483
at the foot of the blessed.

08:03.483 --> 08:04.484
No.

08:06.904 --> 08:10.449
I hope someday you two
have the precious gift

08:10.449 --> 08:13.827
of feeling what I felt for
that beautiful young woman...

08:13.827 --> 08:17.623
[sobs] ...and then to have that
love stolen cruelly from you

08:17.623 --> 08:21.043
by a pitiless God,
and then maybe, just maybe,

08:21.043 --> 08:23.962
you'll remember this day
and your father's anguish

08:23.962 --> 08:26.757
and you'll be ashamed
of the lack of compassion

08:26.757 --> 08:30.177
you showed him
in his time of need.

08:30.177 --> 08:32.888
I love you,
my little brown banana.

08:32.888 --> 08:36.850
I just want you to know.
[sobs]

08:36.850 --> 08:39.311
I don't know how much more
of that I can take

08:39.311 --> 08:42.147
before I stab him in the neck
with a broken beer bottle.

08:44.107 --> 08:46.193
- What are you smiling about?
- I'm happy.

08:46.193 --> 08:48.362
- Can't I be happy?
- No, not about this.

08:48.362 --> 08:50.615
There's absolutely no reason
to be happy about this.

08:50.615 --> 08:52.574
Drugs.

08:52.574 --> 08:54.534
- Are you high?
- No.

08:54.534 --> 08:55.744
- [switchblade clicks]
- [gasps]

08:55.744 --> 08:57.955
Fuck.
Where did you get that?

08:57.955 --> 09:00.123
From Carl's pillow.

09:00.123 --> 09:02.542
Probably has a pipe bomb stashed
in there somewhere too.

09:02.542 --> 09:04.086
We should go visit him
this weekend.

09:04.086 --> 09:05.671
- No, thank you.
- Why not?

09:05.671 --> 09:07.172
- [Debbie] Busy.
- Doing what?

09:07.172 --> 09:09.675
Living my life away from
my degenerate criminal brother

09:09.675 --> 09:11.677
who keeps a switchblade
in his pillow.

09:11.677 --> 09:12.720
Go.
Work.

09:12.720 --> 09:14.888
Can't be late again.

09:14.888 --> 09:16.723
You ready, Debs?

09:16.723 --> 09:18.725
Come on.

09:18.725 --> 09:19.559
Hey, Debs.

09:19.559 --> 09:21.853
Ooh.

09:21.853 --> 09:24.481
Debbie.

09:24.481 --> 09:26.191
I love you.

09:26.191 --> 09:27.693
[laughing]
I just want you to know

09:27.693 --> 09:30.195
I really, really love you.

09:30.195 --> 09:31.780
[laughs]

09:31.780 --> 09:34.783
♪ guitar chord ♪

09:34.783 --> 09:39.788
♪♪♪

10:14.406 --> 10:15.490
Hi.

10:15.490 --> 10:17.451
Hey.

10:17.451 --> 10:20.078
I thought you were gonna
set the alarm.

10:20.078 --> 10:22.414
No, I lied.

10:22.414 --> 10:24.708
- I have a class.
- Yeah, me too.

10:24.708 --> 10:28.003
[sighs] Neo-Marxist philosophy
of the Frankfurt School,

10:28.003 --> 10:29.337
Adorno and Fromm.

10:29.337 --> 10:31.506
Mm.
I love Adorno.

10:31.506 --> 10:34.342
[laughs] You don't even know
who Adorno was.

10:34.342 --> 10:37.763
Theodoro Adorno,

10:37.763 --> 10:39.682
Negative Dialectics,

10:39.682 --> 10:41.975
Minima Moralia.

10:41.975 --> 10:45.729
Now, Adorno advanced
a dialectical conception

10:45.729 --> 10:47.314
of natural history

10:47.314 --> 10:49.191
that critiqued
the twin temptations

10:49.191 --> 10:51.943
of ontology and empiricism

10:51.943 --> 10:54.321
through studies of Kierkegaard
and Husserl.

10:54.321 --> 10:55.655
You remembered that.

10:55.655 --> 10:57.407
I had an excellent professor.

10:57.407 --> 10:58.743
[sighs]

11:01.453 --> 11:03.246
No, stay.

11:03.246 --> 11:06.541
I can't be responsible for
impeding your academic growth.

11:06.541 --> 11:07.918
[sighs] Professor Youens
won't care.

11:07.918 --> 11:10.128
He doesn't show up
half the time.

11:10.128 --> 11:11.714
Well, then you teach.

11:11.714 --> 11:13.965
That's what teacher's assistants
are for.

11:13.965 --> 11:15.801
What, to fill in
for absent professors?

11:15.801 --> 11:17.928
To teach survey courses
to business majors

11:17.928 --> 11:19.387
who don't give a damn.

11:19.387 --> 11:21.181
Oh, he doesn't teach
survey courses.

11:21.181 --> 11:23.725
Applied mathematics
and particle dynamics

11:23.725 --> 11:25.060
for physics majors.

11:25.060 --> 11:26.770
He still drinking his breakfast?

11:26.770 --> 11:30.190
No, he's usually still hammered
from the night before.

11:30.190 --> 11:32.484
You know,
two fluid dynamics majors

11:32.484 --> 11:33.735
reported him to the Dean.

11:33.735 --> 11:35.153
Think he's gonna
get himself fired.

11:35.153 --> 11:37.907
Oh, nobody's firing Dr. Youens.

11:37.907 --> 11:40.700
He's a member of the
National Academy of Sciences.

11:40.700 --> 11:44.162
He's been short-listed
for the Fields Prize four times.

11:44.162 --> 11:46.791
Not to mention he literally
wrote the textbook

11:46.791 --> 11:48.708
he teaches from.

11:48.708 --> 11:51.044
Hey, can I come over tonight?

11:51.044 --> 11:52.880
No.

11:52.880 --> 11:53.756
Why?

11:53.756 --> 11:54.673
I'm busy.

11:54.673 --> 11:56.049
Doing what?
[kiss]

11:59.386 --> 12:02.305
♪ dramatic rock music ♪

12:02.305 --> 12:07.310
♪♪♪

12:21.951 --> 12:22.951
Gallagher.

12:22.951 --> 12:24.953
Here.

12:27.747 --> 12:29.624
You're coming?

12:29.624 --> 12:32.961
- You don't want me to?
- Not really. [chuckles]

12:32.961 --> 12:34.963
Is that okay?
She's only 15.

12:34.963 --> 12:36.256
It's your daughter's choice.

12:36.256 --> 12:38.341
- Sister.
- Sister.

12:38.341 --> 12:39.843
Thanks, but I'll be okay.

12:42.971 --> 12:45.473
Great.
I'll just wait here.

12:45.473 --> 12:46.558
[knocking]

12:46.558 --> 12:47.851
[breathing heavily]

12:47.851 --> 12:50.896
[doorbell rings]

12:50.896 --> 12:53.398
Kev.

12:53.398 --> 12:55.860
Kev.

12:55.860 --> 12:56.651
[exclaims]
What?

12:56.651 --> 12:57.861
Door.

12:57.861 --> 13:00.530
[doorbell rings]

13:00.530 --> 13:01.781
♪ intense music ♪

13:01.781 --> 13:05.619
[baby crying]

13:05.619 --> 13:07.412
- [Kev] It's okay. It's okay.
- [doorbell rings]

13:07.412 --> 13:08.914
Baby, go back to sleep.

13:08.914 --> 13:11.041
It's just some idiot
pounding on the door.

13:11.041 --> 13:12.584
[knocking]

13:12.584 --> 13:15.253
♪♪♪

13:15.253 --> 13:17.380
[doorbell rings]

13:17.380 --> 13:18.215
[knocking]

13:18.215 --> 13:20.133
Shit, I'm coming!

13:20.133 --> 13:23.178
[knocking,
doorbell ringing]

13:25.639 --> 13:27.265
- Oh, good morning.
- Holy shit.

13:27.265 --> 13:29.100
What is with the doorbell?
Somebody dying?

13:29.100 --> 13:31.061
We have a petition
for you to sign.

13:31.061 --> 13:33.730
We are collecting signatures
to force the police

13:33.730 --> 13:35.398
to do something about the noise.

13:35.398 --> 13:37.943
- [engine revving]
- What noise?

13:37.943 --> 13:39.611
- You don't hear that?
- Every morning?

13:39.611 --> 13:41.655
- We've asked him nicely.
- Begged numerous times.

13:41.655 --> 13:42.907
We've called the police.

13:42.907 --> 13:44.074
[sighs]
It's the ghetto.

13:44.074 --> 13:46.243
Lots of noises in the ghetto.

13:46.243 --> 13:48.411
Automatic gunfire,
people begging for their lives.

13:48.411 --> 13:50.872
Okay, it's not the ghetto;
it's our home,

13:50.872 --> 13:54.125
and that Turkish idiot
is doing this on purpose

13:54.125 --> 13:55.627
- because we asked...
- Asked nicely.

13:55.627 --> 13:57.963
- ...that he remove
that rusting car

13:57.963 --> 13:59.965
and rotting sofa
from his yard.

13:59.965 --> 14:02.051
Well, first of all,
Yanis isn't Turkish.

14:02.051 --> 14:03.468
He's Greek

14:03.468 --> 14:05.720
or Albanian
or something,

14:05.720 --> 14:07.890
and that's a Ford Fairlane
he's trying to fix up.

14:07.890 --> 14:08.890
What is going on?

14:08.890 --> 14:10.893
They want Yanis
to clean up his yard.

14:10.893 --> 14:12.018
And stop
the motorcycle noise.

14:12.018 --> 14:13.812
They have a petition
they want us to sign.

14:13.812 --> 14:15.814
- A what?
- Sign here.

14:15.814 --> 14:17.107
Look, I know Yanis
pretty well.

14:17.107 --> 14:19.025
Let me talk to him first,
all right?

14:19.025 --> 14:21.987
Let me--we don't want things
to get dramatic.

14:21.987 --> 14:25.490
Let me see
what I can do, okay?

14:25.490 --> 14:26.992
Okay?

14:26.992 --> 14:28.034
Okay.

14:28.034 --> 14:28.868
♪♪♪

14:28.868 --> 14:30.370
Forty-five,

14:30.370 --> 14:32.789
46,

14:32.789 --> 14:34.374
47,

14:34.374 --> 14:35.500
48,

